3D Editor tools offer important functionalities like packing objects, orientation to the best position and hollowing, beside basic transformations(move, rotate, scale) of imported 3D objects that are listed below.

<img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="3D Editor">
<br>
<br>


## Packing

Packing tool sets space between imported objects and applies to current scene.

## Auto Orientation

Orientation tool automatically rotates the object in order to have minimum surfaces that need support.

> ## Distance to Floor
>
> Distance of objects to floor is set globally, so this parameter affects all actions in the future.
 

## Hollowing Parameters

Hollowing tool is used to make objects hollow in order to use less material. it's three parameters are described below

> ## Thickness
>
> This parameter is the thickness of the walls after hollowing.
>
> ## Consistency
> Description of consistency here.
>
> ## Fill Distance
>
> Filling cheese material in hollowed space.
